hardshare-config 
Manage local and remote configuration

USAGE:
    hardshare config [FLAGS] [OPTIONS] [ID]

FLAGS:
    -c, --create               If no local configuration is found, then create
                               one
    -h, --help                 Prints help information
        --include-dissolved    Include configuration data of dissolved workspace
                               deployments
    -l, --list                 Lists configuration
        --local                Only show local configuration data
    -p, --prune                delete files in local API tokens directory that
                               are not valid; to get list of files with errors,
                               try `--list`
    -V, --version              Prints version information

OPTIONS:
        --cprovider <CPROVIDER>
            select a container provider: lxd, docker, podman, proxy

        --assign-image <IMG>
            assign image for cprovider to use (advanced option)

        --add-token <FILE>         add new API token

ARGS:
    <ID>    id of workspace deployment for configuration changes (can be
            unique prefix); this argument is not required if there is only 1
            workspace deployment

